# Forge Council security

Treat OWASP/NIST GenAI-style risks as first-class: injection, malicious repo instructions, tool abuse, leakage, cross-project memory, cost DoS.

- Scan and update `CONFLICT_MAP.md` before execution-oriented work.
- Obey `_system/forge-council/policies/tool_policy.md` and `approval_policy.md`.
- No secrets in logs, traces, or prompts committed to git.
- Structured outputs for state transitions; reject malformed orchestration payloads.

See `NFR.md` for control IDs (SEC-01–SEC-10).
